### Syntax

The following is the syntax for the Show method.

`Reporting.TaskPane.Hide()`

## Refresh (Task Pane)

> Example:

```vb
Dim bResult As Boolean
bResult = Reporting.TaskPane.IsVisible()
If bResult = True Then
Call Reporting.TaskPane.Refresh()
End If
```

You can use the Refresh method to refresh the Task Pane in your report. To use the Refresh method, there must be an active connection to a TM1 server via the API or the Planning Analytics for Microsoft Excel login.

### Syntax

The following is the syntax for the Refresh method.

`Reporting.TaskPane.Refresh()`

## IsInvisible (Task Pane)

> Example:

```vb
Dim bResult As Boolean
bResult = Reporting.TaskPane.IsVisible()
If bResult = True Then
Call Reporting.TaskPane.Refresh()
End If
```

You can use the IsInvisible method to return the state of the Task Pane. If True is returned, the Task Pane is visible. If False is returned, the Task Pane is not visible. To use the IsInvisible method, there must be an active connection to a TM1 server via the API or the Planning Analytics for Microsoft Excel login.

### Syntax

The following is the syntax for the Refresh method.

`Reporting.TaskPane.IsVisible()`